metadata.title: #### On this page
metadata.content:
Encryption Middleware
Encryption middleware provides end-to-end encryption for events, step output, and function output.
**Only encrypted data is sent to Inngest servers**
: encryption and decryption happen within your infrastructure.
TypeScript (v2.0.0+) Python (v0.3.0+)

metadata.title: #### On this page
#### On this page
metadata.content:
Encryption Middleware
Changing the encrypted event.data field
Only select pieces of event data are encrypted. By default, only the data.encrypted field.
This can be customized using the
```
eventEncryptionField: string
```
setting.

metadata.title: #### On this page
metadata.content:
Encryption Middleware
Decrypt only mode
To disable encryption but continue decrypting, set
```
decryptOnly: true
```
. This is useful when you want to migrate away from encryption but still need to process older events.

metadata.title: #### On this page
#### On this page
metadata.content:
Encryption Middleware
Cross-language support
This middleware is compatible with our encryption middleware in our TypeScript SDK. Encrypted events can be sent from Python and decrypted in TypeScript, and vice versa.
